 * 1일 - first, 2일 - second, 3일 - third / 11- eleventh, 21 - twenty first, twenty second ~, 20- twentieth 30 - thirtieth
 * be(과거) supposed to : ~ 했었야했다.
 * it has been canceled : 취소되었다.
 * be scheduled to ~ : ~ 하기로 예정되어있다. 
 * please keep this in mind : 명심하세요
 * the lecture is from 9 am to 10 am
 * it will start at 9 am and it will finish 10 am

 -> the first is lecture about A. which is from 10 am to 11 am by jackson
     and then, maria will lead lecture about B. it will start a 2pm and it will finish at 3pm 
     
 * the interview with Jhone is ~ : 존광의 인터뷰는 ~
 * you will interview Jhone at 2pm 
 * the first is lecture about A at 11 am in room7, at the same time there will be a lecture about B in room3 you have to choose one
 * both sessions from 11 am to noon simutaneously, so you have to choose one  : 동시에 열리므로 선택해야한다.
 * there will be "programming 2" from 2 pm to 3pm : 2시부터 3시까지 프로그래밍 수업이 있다.
 * lunch will be provided : will be provided  : ~ 될것이다.